Given an image and a list of Danbooru-style tags, determine whether each tag is visually present in the image.

Tags to evaluate:
{{ tags_block }}

For each tag, respond with a JSON array:
[
  {"tag": "tag_name", "present": true, "confidence": 0.95},
  {"tag": "tag_name", "present": false, "confidence": 0.1}
]

Rules:
- "present" means the tag's visual concept is clearly reflected in the image
- "confidence" is your certainty level (0.0 = unsure, 1.0 = certain)
- Camera tags (cowboy_shot, close-up, etc.): evaluate the framing/composition
- Lighting tags (sidelighting, soft_shadow, etc.): evaluate the lighting style
- Mood tags (peaceful, dramatic, etc.): evaluate the overall atmosphere
- Location tags (outdoors, classroom, etc.): evaluate the background/setting
- Respond ONLY with the JSON array, no additional text
